    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-18T11:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-18T11:29:00-05:00" n="267"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/52</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-18T19:00:00+02:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 19, 11.45 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1200. Communicated contents of your 1324, April 16, 5 p.m., to Government which
                    greatly pleased therewith, and desires to make announcement of contents through
                    public prints. I see no objection.</p>
                <p>The plan sent to-day by military attaché to War College in his code is the result
                    of conferences between him and Russian Government.<note n="1" xml:id="d267fn1"
                        >The plan was also received through the Russian Embassy, Apr. 21, <hi
                            rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                    </note> I have conferred on this subject several times with <persName
                        corresp="#p_MPN1">Milyukov</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d267fn2">From
                        March to May 1917 Russian Minister of Foreign Affairs.</note> We approve
                    plan as submitted. Military attaché says approved by Russian war department. I
                    again urge prompt action for improving transportation facilities. Strong
                    practical operating man should be sent Vladivostok immediately, where congestion
                    deplorable and increasing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
